.PP
Example:

.IP
.nf
1> io_ansi:cursor_horizontal_vertical(10, 20).
<<"\\e[10;20f">>

.fi


.RE
.B
\fBcursor_move(DeltaLine :: integer(), DeltaColumn :: integer()) ->\fR
\fB                     unicode:chardata().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Move the cursor relative to its current position.

.PP
Positive \fIDeltaLine\fR moves down, negative moves up. Positive \fIDeltaColumn\fR moves right (forward), negative moves left (backward).

.PP
Example:

.IP
.nf
1> io_ansi:cursor_move(-5, 0).
<<"\\e[5A">>
2> io_ansi:cursor_move(0, 10).
<<"\\e[10C">>
3> io_ansi:cursor_move(3, -2).
<<"\\e[3B\\e[2D">>
4> io_ansi:cursor_move(0, 0).
<<>>

.fi


