.RE
.B
\fBreset() -> unicode:chardata().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Reset virtual terminal sequences to their original state.

.PP
This only resets the things supported by the loaded terminfo database, which means that OSCs such as \fIhyperlink_start/2\fR are not reset but have to be reset by emitting \fIhyperlink_reset/0\fR.

.PP
Example:

.IP
.nf
1> io_ansi:reset().
<<"\\e(B\\e[m">>

.fi


.RE
